			<title>E3 Thread 2015</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?77912-E3-Thread-2015&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2015 03:12:01 GMT</pubDate>
			<description>E3 should be pretty big this year, but it seems like the focus is drifting away from new hardware and first party, and more towards third party games that were noticeable absent from the past two E3s. Notable, there are three additional press conferences this year, including the first ever PC only...</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>E3 should be pretty big this year, but it seems like the focus is drifting away from new hardware and first party, and more towards third party games that were noticeable absent from the past two E3s. Notable, there are three additional press conferences this year, including the first ever PC only press event.<br />
<br />
Starting this thread early, as there are often reveals and leaks before E3 starts, as well as to act as a (small) resource/guide to what you can expect. I'll start off with a summary of the press events, followed by what I think we might actually see at these events. <br />
<br />
