Like Bethesda, the idea is they wouldn't have their own press conference if they didn't have a lot of stuff to show off. I sort of feel like they have been inching towards this with their E3 coverage from last year, so am not expecting anything earth shattering, but between Square-Enix and Eidos, they should have a lot of stuff.<br />
<ul><li style="">Eidos</li><li style="">Tomb Raider - Extended look from what you get at the Microsoft event.</li><li style="">New Deux Ex, already announced. Show gameplay.</li><li style="">Just Cause 3, already announced. Show gameplay.</li><li style="">Possibly a new Hitman.</li><li style="">SE likes to experiment with turning Eidos properties into F2P and mmo style games. Triad Wars for example, the Sleeping Dogs spinoff, hasn't been shown yet.</li><li style="">Small chance at Legacy of Kain/Soul Reaver revival. <br />
