Square Enix</li><li style="">Dragon Quest - They have a few of these in the works, they could show one. The two off the top of my head are a Dynasty Warriors style game, and a Theaterhythm game.</li><li style="">Bravely Default Sequel - They have been promoting this a lot in Japan. Could be worth a mention and a trailer.</li><li style="">Star Ocean - A new one of these was recently announced. They could start promoting it.</li><li style="">Final Fantasy 15 - I think they have said they will not show it at E3 this year. It's got to be close to done though.</li><li style="">Kingdom Hearts 3 - I will be surprised if they show this. I think it's too early still. Maybe a trailer though.</li><li style="">Final Fantasy Type 0 PC port<br />
</li></ul><br />
<br />
<b>PC Gaming</b><br />
<br />
At 3 hours, I think this one has the biggest potential for being a flop. It's the first time they have had a PC press conference for E3, but it isn't the first time something similar has been tried elsewhere. Still, if you are a PC stalwart, there will surely be a few things you find interesting.<br />
<br />
I don't know exactly what they might be showing, so I'll list what these companies are known for. This is the guest list from what I understand:<br />
<ul><li style="">Day[9] - Starcraft 2 commentator. Will be hosting.</li><li style="">Blizzard Entertainment - They have their own event, so instead of new announcements, I expect them to talk about stuff we already know about. That shooter they are making, for example.</li><li style="">Microsoft Studios - Windows 10 and DX12 talk. Maybe Fable Legends. Maybe Halo collection. (I hope)</li><li style="">Bohemia Interactive - They make ARMA 3, so something similar I guess?</li><li style="">Paradox Interactive - They make a lot of smaller PC titles. Wiki suggests something called Hollowpoint, previously announced, which I've never heard of.</li><li style="">Obsidian Entertainment - Big rpg guys. I don't know what they could show. They just released Pillars of Eternity.</li><li style="">Tripwire Interactive - Killing Floor 2, most likely. Very popular with the PC shooter crowd.</li><li style="">ArenaNet - I don't follow Guild Wars 2 lately. New expansion? Guild Wars 3? Dunno.</li><li style="">The Creative Assembly - Total War Warhammer. I forgot to tell you guys this got announced. I'm sorry.</li><li style="">Frictional Games - Known for horror cult classic Amnesia. Working on something called Soma? Not familiar.</li><li style="">Frontier Developments - Elite Dangerous</li><li style="">SCS Software - Blank Truck Simulator</li><li style="">Splash Damage - Dirty Bomb. Team based shooter from the people who made Brink.</li><li style="">Square Enix - Maybe ports they didn't have time to show in their own event, or that tech demo from the last big PC conference.</li><li style="">Cloud Imperium Games - Star Citizen</li><li style="">Devolver Digital - They make a lot of solid indie games, so something like that.</li><li style="">A few developers were called out by name, though I only remember one off the top of my head, and don't know what they might present.<br />
</li></ul><br />
